Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} and @parsnip{1}(trimmed, peeled, and cut on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces). Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce}(peeled and diced into ½-inch pieces). Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}(minced until you have 2 TBSP). Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped).

Toss carrots and parsnip on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

Meanwhile, place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15%minutes}.

Drain and return potatoes to pot. Mash with @butter{1%tbsp} and @milk{6.75%ounce} until smooth and creamy.

> TIP: If necessary, add more milk a splash at a time.

Stir in @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and season with salt and pepper.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Brown Butter Veggies ==

While potatoes cook, melt @butter{2%tbsp} in a #medium nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring frequently, until butter is foamy and flecked with amber brown bits, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat and carefully transfer brown butter to a #large bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

== Beef ==

Pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} to rest. Wash out pan.

== Shallot Pan Sauce ==

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in same pan over medium-low heat. Add minced shallot and cook until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @beef demi-glace{1}, @water{1/4%cup}, and any resting juices from beef. Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir in another @butter{1%tbsp}; season with salt and pepper.

Add carrots, parsnip, and half the parsley to bowl with brown butter; toss to thoroughly coat.

== To Serve ==

Divide veggies, mashed potatoes, and beef between plates. Top beef with sauce and remaining parsley. Serve.